gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: B
task: B4
title: "bug(assemblies): assembly.missing_index floods Sentry — fix fingerprint (#1370)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P2
refs:
  - CROP-front#1370
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  assembly.missing_index errors use a per-assembly fingerprint, creating a new
  Sentry issue + email alert for every single broken assembly. This floods Sentry
  with noise and buries real signals. Underlying nav-resolution failures remain
  unaddressed. Fix in two parts:
  1. Consolidate fingerprint: group all assembly.missing_index under one Sentry
     issue (fingerprint on error type, not assembly id).
  2. Document the underlying nav-resolution failures as a follow-up issue if not
     already tracked.

scope:
  in:
    - Locate assembly.missing_index Sentry capture/throw site
    - Override fingerprint: ['assembly.missing_index'] (remove assembly-specific key)
    - Verify in Sentry staging: multiple assemblies → single issue, not N issues
    - Check if underlying nav-resolution root cause is tracked; file follow-up if not
  out:
    - Fixing the underlying nav-resolution failures (separate scope)
    - Changing assembly data or fetch logic

acceptance:
  - assembly.missing_index events group under a single Sentry issue
  - No per-assembly email storm on next occurrence
  - Root cause follow-up issue exists (existing or newly filed)

dep: none
output: Sentry capture site patched (fingerprint override) + follow-up issue link in PR
